can allergies cause lymph node in the back of the neck to swell can allergies cause lymph node in the back of the neck to swell i had this happen to me i had an isolated lymph node to swell on the side of my neck the doctor told me it really wasn't anything to worry about and that i could be fighting against an infection you could have some kind of infection though if you have any other symptoms such as pain anywhere or a fever later after talking to the md that day i found a tick on my head my head had been sore and then days after we pulled the tick off the lymph node went down i had to take an antibiotic just for precaution but anyway i would absolutely not worry about it unless it persists and then see a dr if you have any other signs symptoms like mentioned above pain or fever or sore throat hope this helped Non-Hodgkin's lymphoma Group A streptococcal infection Pharyngitis Infectious mononucleosis Lymph node Chronic fatigue syndrome Prostate cancer Stomach cancer Tuberculosis First aid Bubonic plague Lyme disease Diphtheria Lymphatic system Hodgkin's lymphoma Mouth ulcer Kawasaki disease Cancer of the larynx Traumatic brain injury Breast cancer Conjunctivitis Hay fever Scrofula Rocky Mountain spotted fever Ebola Leukemia Ehrlichiosis Lymphogranuloma venereum Erysipelas Chancroid Cephalexin Severe Acute Respiratory Syndrome Cancer Malignant melanoma Herpesviridae Mumps Allergy Cytomegalovirus Chronic lymphocytic leukemia Common cold Eczema Psoriasis Appendicitis Lupus erythematosus Asthma Toxoplasmosis Hip fracture Gonorrhoea Rheumatic fever Colorectal cancer Boil Sulfasalazine Pneumonia Encephalitis Black Death Diarrhea Sleeping sickness Streptococcus Cellulitis Esophageal cancer Monkeypox Tick Q fever Soft tissue sarcoma Upper respiratory tract infection Thyroid cancer Virus AIDS Humphrey Bogart Poliomyelitis Sexually-transmitted infection Metastasis Typhoid fever Cervical cancer Penile cancer Echovirus Domestic rabbit Herpes simplex virus Acute lymphoblastic